git init:           To start a new repository.
git clone:          To obtain a repository from an existing url.
git add .           Add files to the staging area.
git commit :        Records the files permanently in the version history.
git commit -a :     To commit any file thats is added by git add command.

git commit -am "<message>" :  To set the description with the commit function.

git status :        Lists the files that have to be committed.
git branch :        Lists all local branches in the current repository.
git branch -a       Lista all branches including the hidden ones.
git branch -d:      It deletes the feature branch.
git checkout:       To switch from one branch to another.

git branch <branchname>:       It creates a new branch with the specified branch name.

git checkout -be:   Creates a new branch and also switches to it.
git merge:          Merges the specified branch history into the current branch.
git push:           It sends the commited changes of the branch to the repository.
git pull:           It fetches and merges the changes from the server to the current directory.
